            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#eisenbergK" start="849.416" end="x">To cover them with coal. When they were covered with coal, he was standing [there], and he laughed. He laughed at us. He smiled, and afterwards he ordered us not to dig them up. They should come up by themselves. And if they cannot come up, they can remain there, too.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="864.450" end="x">Hm.</span>
