        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="x" end="x">This happened in your <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Kalman Eisenberg</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#eisenbergK" start="x" end="x">This [happened] in our <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>, in <a class="placename" href="#vothC132" type="camp">Starachowice</a>. Afterwards happened when one women, after being in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> four months, gave birth to a child...After having been four months in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> she gave birth to this child. And an order came that the child is not permitted to live more than two days. If the child will live two days, the mother, too, will be shot. Then there were instances when from lack of cleanliness and from hunger many people became sick with typhus. Finding this out, the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>...that people are sick with typhus, he came into...into the <a class="term" href="#vothG_block">block</a> where the sick lay and shot these people in their beds. There was a group...the first group [consisted] of twenty people. A month later the sick became more numerous. There were fifty.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
